<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-09-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-09-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="470" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d470">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Newberry</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-09-09"><hi rend="italic">September 9,
                            1892</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Newberry states that he has been paid £600 as a settlement of the
                        Bartlett case, and that the demands of the United States have been complied
                        with.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>